Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nhere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go around and say hello to\Npeople.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.32,0:01:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I need gay worthy.\N>> Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.79,0:01:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm dressed like a dude today, huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.24,0:01:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'm uh These are my dude duds.\N>> Cool dude duds. You like them?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.08,0:01:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, yeah.\N>> New jacket and everything. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.88,0:01:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. Hi. How you?\NUhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.15,0:01:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\N>> Ah, there we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.92,0:01:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hey.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.79,0:01:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Nice to meet you. Thank you.\N>> Yeah. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.36,0:01:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You can leave the music on. It's okay.\N>> You can leave the music on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.68,0:02:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi. How are you?\N>> We're not letting go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.47,0:02:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hey.\N>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.84,0:02:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.\N>> God bless.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.44,0:02:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Michigan friends are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.87,0:02:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Michigan friends are here.\N>> Michiganis, huh? Michiganis, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.72,0:02:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Michiganis\N>> and Ianis.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.52,0:02:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Wisconsin.\N>> Wisconsinis.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.31,0:02:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Colorado over here. Colorado is\N>> I was from Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.36,0:02:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Australia.\N>> Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.36,0:02:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> Oh, how wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.76,0:02:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Australia.\N>> I don't know how those people survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.23,0:02:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't fall off the planet. You\Nknow,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.64,0:02:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> they're upside down. What keeps them on\Nthe planet? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.36,0:02:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think we're on top.\N>> Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.92,0:03:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, sweetheart.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.59,0:03:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll start from the ending as as is our\Ncustom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.95,0:03:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody starts from the beginning. And\Nhow far does it get them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.64,0:03:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to go from here to there? Why\Nnot just go there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:04:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we start from there.\NThis is a subtlety.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.23,0:04:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a contextualization.\NAnd if you get it, it'll save you 500
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.40,0:04:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes.\NEverything is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.63,0:04:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is spontaneously being what\Nit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.12,0:04:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All what appears to be consequences of\Nthat are the consequence of that which
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.00,0:04:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not that which it does.\NUh all things are happening
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously.\NNothing is being caused by anything
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.12,0:04:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,else. Everything is only just being what\Nit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.91,0:04:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of that which it is\Neverything around it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.56,0:04:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is correlated\Nas a consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.72,0:05:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The you the person that you think you\Nare doesn't cause anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.36,0:05:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening spontaneously.\NYou say but what about when I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.68,0:05:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,deliberate? You're spontaneously\Ndeliberate idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.47,0:05:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What about when I make a decision?\NYou're spontaneously making a decision
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.12,0:05:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is the consequence of that which you\Nare.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.24,0:05:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything radiates forth. the energy\Nof that which it is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.44,0:05:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which interacts with\Nthe presence and the energy of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.44,0:05:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,everything else that is.\NSo what you're seeing then is an
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.32,0:05:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction\Nas a consequence of that which
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.28,0:05:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,everything is.\NThe reason of behind all that is the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.47,0:06:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite field of consciousness which is\Neverywhere present beyond time and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,location\Nwhich is nonlinear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.36,0:06:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite power.\Nof such dimension as to be beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.75,0:06:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehension.\NThis lifetime was unusual
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from a statistical viewpoint\Nand um rather profound experiences began
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.80,0:06:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely early in life. First one was\Nat age three
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.03,0:06:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and then later in life in teenage\Nuh there was a huge storm. I was out in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:06:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the country, Wisconsin,\Nyou know, like zero blizzard, no lights
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.91,0:07:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,on. There was no electric on the highway\Nand uh I just wanted to get out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.68,0:07:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,wind. So there was a huge snowbank. So I\Njust dug a little place, you know, just
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to get out of the wind. I wasn't near\Ndeath or anything. I was just, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.63,0:07:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,cold as all get out.\NAnd I just uh got out of the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.36,0:07:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a phenomena,\Nan incredible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of love overtook everything.\NAll uh personal self disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.36,0:07:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only the infinite presence of\Nlove which is what you are and in that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.36,0:08:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,condition which lasted outside of time\Nwas
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.63,0:08:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinity of foreverness\Nin the realization that that which I am
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.52,0:08:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,existed before all universes and will\Nexist after all universes have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.80,0:08:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,disappeared.\NLet's see if that is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.52,0:08:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that word.\NResist. That is absolute truth. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.36,0:08:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the absolute truth.\NIf that's the absolute truth for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.40,0:08:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then it is for you also.\NUh so
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.03,0:08:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence then wiped out all\Nthinkingness, all thought, all mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a condition that later recurred\Nand we necessitated leaving the world
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.08,0:09:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly.\NAnd at that time Sedona was a small
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.72,0:09:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,town, 3,000 people, no stop lightss and\Nno lights in town after dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.64,0:09:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There was one restaurant in town open in\Nthe winter closed at 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.88,0:09:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nuh that condition then prevailed and it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.92,0:09:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was no longer possible to function in\Nthe world and uh to walk away from a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.72,0:09:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,rather incredible lifestyle and uh and I\Nbought a cat a cot in the dime store
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh some bidding and um\Nthe charity place and some silverware.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.64,0:09:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the refrigerator, I had a piece\Nof cheese and a six-ack of Pepsi. And
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.80,0:09:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what more did you need?\NI lived that way for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.76,0:09:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally, there would be a\Ncelebration, an apple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.51,0:10:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, we'll have an apple.\NGreat excitement in the monastery there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.08,0:10:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it was a monastery. Monastery for\None.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.24,0:10:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can remember in the monastery uh\Nit was actually built somewhat like a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mon monastery and uh and walked past a\Nmirror and I was shocked to see somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.60,0:10:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,was in the in the building.\NThose are just fun things to talk about,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.07,0:10:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NBut um
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.12,0:10:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in the snowbank was the first at age\Nthree was the experience of the void.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.12,0:10:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that's where I ended up in\Nprior lifetimes at the void. The pathway
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of negation will take you to the void\Nand I warn about it in the books that I
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.00,0:10:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,write. The one I'm completing\Ntranscending levels of consciousness is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.44,0:10:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,almost edited and devotional on duality\Nthe first draft is done and in both of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.07,0:11:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,them I point out that a calibration\Nlevel 850 if you assiduously follow the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.27,0:11:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway of negation uh you will end up\Nat nothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.60,0:11:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothingness\Nis not the ultimate state of the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.20,0:11:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,believers to the contrary. It is\Nnothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.20,0:11:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear,\Ninfinite and profound
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.76,0:11:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and incredible.\NWithout forewarning, without prior
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.64,0:11:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge, one would assume this is the\Ngreat state of enlightenment itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.07,0:11:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, many people did go as far\Nas 850 and stop there. And they probably
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.07,0:11:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are nowhere.\NThey're not thinking, of course, but are
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.24,0:11:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,hung up in the void. Yeah.\NYeah. If the void was real, you could
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.80,0:11:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,stay there. It's not real. That's why\NI'm alive today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.80,0:12:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Go transcend that error, you know. Yeah.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the secret to it was the experience in\Nthe snowbank because in the snowbank
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.44,0:12:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there was also nonlinear nothingness, no\Nnothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.60,0:12:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,just an infinite field like the radiance\Nof sun. You might say, the radiance of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.12,0:12:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the sun.\NBut one of the most impressive things
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.32,0:12:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,about this quality of love was its\Ninfinite power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.48,0:12:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Its infinite power. And we talked about\Nthe power of the infinite field of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.72,0:12:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.39,0:12:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of love then when when you\Nreach the ultimate state the the quality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.00,0:12:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of love is profound. It's nothingness.\NIt's nothingness. It's void except for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.60,0:12:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of love which is\Noverwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.36,0:12:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the quality of that love is it's\Ninfinitely powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.07,0:13:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisitely gentle. It like melts you\Nwith its exquisite
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.00,0:13:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,presence.\NAnd its power simultaneously is infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.95,0:13:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and like rock. Nobody knows that except\Nsomebody who's been there. That is soft
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.44,0:13:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and exquisite\Nand simultaneously its power is like
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.24,0:13:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,rock.\NAnd what do I mean by that? I mean that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.95,0:13:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it's\N>> sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> irresistible.\N>> Is that better?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.32,0:13:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> How were your last moments on this\Nplanet? Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.16,0:13:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, everything happens as a\Nconsequence of that which they are. As a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.32,0:13:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of that which she is. She\Nautomatically does things. As a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.44,0:13:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of that which I am,\NI automatically do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.51,0:14:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no say about it.\NAnd neither does she.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.00,0:14:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence, I can't make her wrong\Nbecause she's not responsible for her
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.48,0:14:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,own behavior either.\NShe's just being who she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.63,0:14:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. Thank goodness.\NI don't know. I would would have gotten
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.60,0:14:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,here today otherwise\Nthis way the door. Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.00,0:14:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Before I lecture the the state\Nresumes and so I've had to learn how to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.88,0:14:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,be in the world and same time in that\Npresence simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.00,0:14:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All things are only being that which\Nthey are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.32,0:14:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't help being what they are at\Nthe moment
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:15:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because as a consequence of that which\Nthey were, they are now that which they
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.60,0:15:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,are\NAmericans, the western world doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.83,0:15:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,understand karma. Unfortunately,\Nkarma is the totality, complete totality
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.44,0:15:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of everything that preceded this moment.\NThe last moment was part of the karma of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,this moment.\NIt's transmitted
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically\Nthrough genetic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.68,0:15:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an accident. You just happen to\Nget born in a certain place or with a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.16,0:15:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,certain\Ndisability or whatever. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.80,0:15:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you research it, you'll find\Neverybody is what they are as a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.88,0:15:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of that which they were.\NThey couldn't help being what they were
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.60,0:15:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,when they were that. Nor can they help\Nbeing what they are now. See
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.39,0:15:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence. There's no point in\Nvilifying everybody because they are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.48,0:16:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,only being what they can be at the\Nmoment. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah, I always say, but hypothetically\Nthey could be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.68,0:16:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Could\Nbe more peanut butter on the sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.68,0:16:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NAll right. It's It's important then for
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiveness. People try to forgive. You\Ncan't really forgive somebody you still
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.80,0:16:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,see as evil. You know,\Nyou can forgive them for being evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.80,0:16:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be evil.\NHowever you see him, it's okay to see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.39,0:16:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,him that way. Okay. So, you don't have\Nto make yourself wrong. They make
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.27,0:16:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself wrong, you get stuck in it.\NTherefore, however you see it is however
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.68,0:16:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it because you're only being\Nwhat you can be at the moment, too. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.51,0:16:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you're only being what they can be. And\Nyou're only being what you can be. As a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.56,0:16:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of that which you become,\Nphenomena are influenced and radiated
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.24,0:17:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,out\Nfor eternity. Right? Eternity. What you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,do has consequences for eternity.\NIndeed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you do\Nhas consequences forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.36,0:17:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, man. That's scary, isn't it?\NWell, we not we notice that the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.79,0:17:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,field of consciousness records all that\Nhappens, all this thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.95,0:17:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It It's all knowing. It's omnipresent.\NOmnipresent. It records everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.67,0:17:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Every hair on one's head is literally\Ncounted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.08,0:17:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as a consequence, you know, like a\NCD or whatever they call those things
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.24,0:17:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,nowadays, you've inherited this disc\Nwhen you get here
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.91,0:17:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you push the on button and this\Nthis lifetime begins to play. Huh.
